# User Registration Input Validation Flow:

01. User Registration form par Sign Up button par click kiya.
   - form tag me <form action="<%=ORSView.USER_REGISTRATION_CTL%>" method="post"> 

02. Request UserRegistrationCtl par gayi aur sabse pehle BaseCtl ki service() method call hui.

03. service() method me request se operation parameter nikala gaya.

04. Agar operation null nahi hai tabhi validate(request) method call hota hai.

05. validate() method parent (BaseCtl) ka nahi balki child class (UserRegistrationCtl) ka call hota hai (method overriding).

06. validate() method (UserRegistrationCtl me) me har input field ki validation start hui.

07. firstName ko check kiya:
    - agar null → "firstName is required"
    - agar invalid format → "Invalid First Name"

08. lastName ko check kiya:
    - null aur valid name check kiya

09. login ko check kiya:
    - null aur email format validate kiya

10. password ko check kiya:
    - null check
    - length (8–12) check
    - pattern (uppercase, lowercase, digit, special char) check

11. confirmPassword ko check kiya:
    - null check kiya

12. password aur confirmPassword ko compare kiya:
    - agar match nahi → error set kiya

13. gender ko check kiya:
    - null check kiya

14. dob ko check kiya:
    - null check
    - valid date format check kiya

15. mobileNo ko check kiya:
    - null check
    - 10 digit length check
    - valid mobile format check kiya

16. Har validation fail hone par:
    - request.setAttribute("fieldName", "error message") set kiya gaya
    - pass = false kiya gaya

17. Agar koi bhi validation fail hoti hai to validate() method false return karta hai.

18. BaseCtl.service() me:
    - ServletUtility.forward(getView(), request, response) call hota hai
    - request wapas JSP par forward hoti hai

19. JSP par:
    - ServletUtility.getErrorMessage("key", request) se error messages show hote hain
